<div id="descriptionContainer">
  
      <div id="description" class="readable stacked" style="right:0">
        
<span id="freeTextContainer1324808013371809497"><i>The Lottery</i>, one of the most terrifying stories written in this century, created a sensation when it was first published in <i>The</i> <i>New Yorker</i>. &quot;Power and haunting,&quot; and &quot;nights of unrest&quot; were typical reader responses. This collection, the only one to appear during Shirley Jackson&apos;s lifetime, unites &quot;The Lottery:&quot; with twenty-four equally unusual stories. Together they demons</span>
  <span id="freeText1324808013371809497" style="display:none"><i>The Lottery</i>, one of the most terrifying stories written in this century, created a sensation when it was first published in <i>The</i> <i>New Yorker</i>. "Power and haunting," and "nights of unrest" were typical reader responses. This collection, the only one to appear during Shirley Jackson's lifetime, unites "The Lottery:" with twenty-four equally unusual stories. Together they demonstrate Jackson's remarkable range--from the hilarious to the truly horrible--and power as a storyteller.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1324808013371809497" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

